post_text:
Please use this link to view the West Springfield Reopening Plan and FAQ. This document will continually be updated as new information is gathered.
August 5, 2020, 6:15 p.m. - In a joint meeting, the School Committee, and our Board of Health will be holding a listening session to gather community input on the re-opening plan. Please know that this is strictly a listening session and not a question and answer due to the high volume of expected calls. Each person will have a maximum of 5 minutes to share their thoughts. Superintendent Connor will send the call-in link to the community by tomorrow morning.
August 10, 2020, 6:00 p.m. - School Committee will take a formal vote on the 20-21 Reopening Model.
Thank you for your continued support!

The Town of West Springfield wants to ensure that everyone‚Äôs voices are heard in an effort to make a change in a broken system. In West Springfield, we work hard every day to make sure our residents are protected.

As a community, we have an opportunity to open a dialogue across our schools, families, community members, elected officials, employees, and interfaith leaders to address institutional and systemic racism head-on and have a positive impact on OUR community. The dialogue must go beyond a meeting in a‚Ä¶

post_text:
Check out this excellent initiative from one of our WSHS student leaders, Meghan Pinter, President of the Rachel's Table Teen Board. Meghan writes, "Our mission is to reduce food waste and alleviate hunger in Western Massachusetts. This spring, we are having our bi-annual Outrun Hunger 5K. Due to the Covid-19 pandemic, it has become a virtual 5k event including an individual walk/step challenge. We are raising money for area food banks, soup kitchens, and food pantries, which is especially important during these unprecedented times. We are trying to get this message out to as many people as possible to raise awareness of this widespread issue."

Visit this registration link to participate:
https://runsignup.com/Race/MA/Springfield/OutrunHunger5k

Mayor Will Reichelt Town of West Springfield West Springfield Health Department

post_text: A great exercise for all of us... every day!
shared_text:
Coburn Counseling Connolly-Willemain
April 13 at 12:30 PM ¬∑

üíôHappy Monday, Coburn Family!üíô

On Mondays we like to focus on mindfulness and coping skills. If you are feeling stuck inside on this raining day and need a break...try this trick!

Below I have included one of my favorite grounding exercises - 5,4,3,2,1. It is a little game I like to use with students when they need a break or to manage some feelings of anxiousness. We use each of our senses to re-center. Often we can regroup and get back to what we were doing right after!

What are....
5Ô∏è‚É£things you can üëÄ SEE from where you are right now?
4Ô∏è‚É£ things you can ‚úãTOUCH?
3Ô∏è‚É£ things you can üëÇhear?
2Ô∏è‚É£ things you can üëÉsmell?
1Ô∏è‚É£ thing you can üëÖtaste?

*You might notice my order is different from the photo below. You can try whichever you like!

text: Mayor Reichelt sits down with newly appointed Superintendent Tim Connor for and update on how the schools are handling COVID 19.

post_text:
Please see the message below from our newly-appointed Superintendent, Tim Connor.

The West Springfield School Committee met this morning to discuss and vote on April vacation in light of the current reality we are facing. In collaboration with the West Springfield Education Association, the vote was to cancel the April vacation and continue remote learning. This time will then be deducted off our scheduled last day of school which was June 22, 2020.

The last day of school will now be June 16, 2020, for Grades 1-11 and June 11, 2020, for Grades EC and Kindergarten.

Schools/Remote Learning will be closed tomorrow April 10, in observance of Good Friday, and April 20, 2020, in observance of Patriots Day.

Meal Distribution:
We will not have meal distribution tomorrow, April 10, or April 20, but we will have meal distribution throughout the remainder of April vacation week. A huge thank you to our awesome cafeteria workers and our Food Service Director, Dario Nardi!

Thank you so much Sophia for all your hard work, this is very much appreciated!

post_text:
Please read the update from the Massachusetts Interscholastic Athletic Association (MIAA) below:

The MIAA Board of Directors voted today, March 16, 2020, to amend the start of the 2020 spring sports season in light of recent mandates from Governor Baker and recommendations from governing health agencies. The updated start date for the 2020 spring season is April 27, 2020.

Additionally, the MIAA Board of Directors voted to have completion of regular season and tournament games by June 20, 2020 with consideration of June 21, 2020 for weather and facility needs.

Details regarding the structure of the spring season will be addressed by the Tournament Management Committee (TMC). An update will be provided and reviewed by the Board by March 25, 2020.

These decisions are based on available information and are made in the best interest of our student-athletes, schools and communities. These decisions will be revisited and adjusted as needed.

Thank you for your patience while dealing with this very fluid situation. Be well.

February 20 at 1:00 PM ¬∑ West Springfield, MA ¬∑

West Springfield High School Traffic Changes

Please be advised after February break the rear access road will no longer be open for traffic except by authorized school department vehicles. Any students, parents, or staff that were using this road in the morning will need use the Piper Road entrance only. The road will also be limited to one way traffic for all vehicles (down from Clark Field towards the high school). Appropriate signage designating the road's use and direction will go up over break.

Tonight the School Committee is holding a public forum at 6:30 p.m., in the Municipal Office Building auditorium. The purpose of the forum is to give an overview of the law passed in late 2019 - the Student Opportunity Act - answer questions, and give people a chance to have their voices heard.

The passage of the Student Opportunity Act (SOA) was designed to ensure that all students will have access to an excellent education. Districts must use these resources (funds) to close the "persistent opportunity and achievement gaps [that] remain for our students of color, low-income students, English learners, and students with disabilities," according to an update from Jeffrey Riley,‚Ä¶ More

post_text: Dr. Ruth Potee will speak in West Springfield next Thursday, January 23! We hope to see you there!
shared_text:
EVENTBRITE.COM
Community Conversation with Dr. Ruth Potee

West Springfield CARE Coalition
January 15 at 11:35 AM ¬∑

Join us at the West Springfield High School on Thursday, January 23rd as we welcome Dr. Ruth Potee to present, The Physiology of Addiction: Effects of Drug-Taking Behavior on the Brain. Doors open at 5:30!

Dr. Potee is a board certified Family Physician and Addiction Medicine Physician who works in western Massachusetts. In addition to her role as a physician and Dr. Potee gives thoughtful, well-researched talks on addiction, substance use, and the development of the teenage brain, to communities across New England. For more information and to register for this must-see event click here: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/community-conversation-with-dr-ruth-potee-tickets-82238484521

post_text: Reminder - the deadline for submitting nominations for the 2020 Excellence in Teaching Award is Friday, January 17! Please submit nominations to the building principal.

West Springfield Public Schools - MA
December 19, 2019 at 1:52 PM ¬∑

The 2020 Pioneer Valley Excellence in Teaching Award nominations are due January 17, 2020. Nominations may be submitted by administrators, teachers, staff, parents, students, and community members.

Please submit the teacher's name with supporting evidence to the building principal by January 17. A Nomination Form may be used, but it is not required.

Five WSPS teachers, including one new teacher, will be honored at a banquet to be held at the Log Cabin in May.

Please see the message below from the WSHS Class of 2021 advisers regarding their apparel sales fundraiser through a local company, Team Sports. The flyer was distributed widely through the district so it is our hope that this message reaches people!

‚ÄúThe Class of 2021 was planning to run apparel sales through a company in town. We learned that they went out of business in the month that we were working with them and unfortunately will not be able to host the sale. The Class of 2021 is working on getting this going through another company.
The Class of 2021 officers and advisers apologize for any confusion/issues this may have caused.‚Äù Thank you.
